  "prompt": "Is spot counselling for reserved candidates?",
  "response": "Spot counseling is often provided as a last opportunity for candidates, including those from reserved categories, to secure a seat in educational institutions. However, the specific details regarding eligibility, guidelines, and processes for spot counseling can vary based on the institution, state regulations, and the educational program.\n\nIn many cases, reserved candidates may have a reserved quota during spot counseling as well, but this depends on the policies of the specific institution or the regulatory body overseeing the admissions process. It's essential to check the official notifications or guidelines released by the relevant education authority or institution to understand the specific provisions for reserved categories during spot counseling.\n\nIf you're looking for information related to a specific institution or context, please provide more details, and I can help clarify further!",
